rComments: He's a great professor and I love his teaching methods. He remembers his students and is very easy to talk with. His exams are just like his practice exams. I went to the lectures so studying was very minimal for me. I took Math 231 with him since he is the best.
Prof J's awesome. He does his job and he does it so well that I lack the words to describe it. Simply the best. His exams are very fair and straightforward.

He is the nicest guy and makes lectures fun, interesting, and helpful. Super friendly when it comes to asking questions or wanting extra help. I emailed him several times about homework questions and he thanked me for asking him!!
His accent is too good. It is a difficult course but he makes it seem easy.
handsome and nice

One of the best professors I've had at university so far. His explanations of mathematical concepts were easy to understand and to the point. However, the course could've, and should've, been a bit more challenging. The professor only covered the bare minimum necessary to pass the class and gave tests that were outrageously easy to inflate grades.

I started the semester extremely afraid of my calculus class. But it turned out to be the best class I've taken thus far in college and I would say that it was not due to the material but to Javid's nature as a teacher. Starting this summer I'm taking the necessary classes to obtain a math minor, largely due to his class.
I really enjoyed this class. I feel like I learned a lot from it. There was a good balance that made the class both fun and challenging at the same time.

I took Calc II with Javid! He prepares students for every exam! He knows how to teach, and you won't be bored in class because he cracks joke so often! If you go to every lecture and discussion like I did and study the practice exams, you won't get a bad grade!!
The best professor ever. I took calc 1 and 2 with him because he is awesome and funny. I enjoy attending classes + I understand very well from him.
Had him for Calc I and I made sure I got into his calc 2 class. If you get a chance take calc with him. He knows what hes talking about and makes sure we understand it. You'll be missed!

The man can teach. If you work hard, you will do great. Plain and simple. Prof J. is funny and he definitely prepares you for the exams with the hw and the discussion material. Overall, if you have a chance to have him as a teacher, do it.

What an awesome professor!  I took Javid for Calc I, and I modified my entire schedule to get into his section for Calc II.  He gives crystal-clear explanations, and I love how he takes the time to derive almost every formula we use, but in an understandable manner.  He also loves to tell jokes and throw candy to students!  We'll miss you at UIUC!
Professor Validashti has a positive attitude during lectures. He is understanding and friendly towards students. The class itself was also great overall and his explanation of calculus II was clear.
Great professor, I like him
Great teacher.
Prepares you very well for the exams and is understanding of what students struggle with.

He's my favorite professor/teacher to date. He enjoys what he does and is always positive during lecture. His exams are very fair and he prepares you with challenging work prior to the exams. If you put the effort into fully understanding the homework, the exams will be a breeze.

Professor J is extremely charming and charismatic, he makes coming to lecture enjoyable and has no problem clarifying when asked. His exams are extremely fair, and not much is required from you in terms of homework. As a freshman, it's safe to say he is my favorite professor, and having him is worth the 8 am discussion.
He's awesome!! Can't say enough good things about him!
